Def:-The COUNT() function returns the number of rows, that matches a specified criterion.
Syntax:-
SELECT COUNT(column-name)
FROM table_name
WHERE condition;

Ex:-Find the total number of products in the Products table:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM Products;

Ex:-Find the number of products where Price is higher than 20:
SELECT COUNT(ProductID)
FROM Products
WHERE Price > 20;

Ex:-Specify Column
SELECT COUNT(ProductName)
FROM Products;

Ex:-Ignore Duplicates
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Price)
FROM Products;

Ex:-Use an Alias(Given the column_name By using AS Keyword).
SELECT COUNT(*) AS [number of records]
FROM Products;

